{"id":"math120-defint210-002","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Antiderivatives and Integrals","subtopic":"Definite integrals","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Find the area under the curve f(x) = x^{n} from x = {lo} to x = {hi}.","params":{"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":2},"lo":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":1},"hi":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":4}},"answer_expr":"defint210","steps":["Area = integral from {lo} to {hi} of x^{n} dx = [x^{n+1}/({n+1})] from {lo} to {hi}.","= ({hi_pow} - {lo_pow}) / ({n+1}) = {answer_defint210} square units."],"tags":["survey-calculus","area","definite-integral","geometry"]}
